snippet.textDisplay: I cant believe people believe that tablet is a "get rid of a baby" pill.  First of all, there are drug requirements through the federal government. Second, once your egg has bonded with a sperm and attached to the uterus, you are pregnant...and no over the counter pill is going to cause you to have an abortion, because that's what it would be...an abortion. As opposed to the morning after pill which may prevent a pregnancy from occurring.  Third...if you are taking a pregnancy test and it comes back positive, it is too late to stop a pregnancy, you are probably at minimum 2 weeks pregnant.   If you choose not to carry the baby, you would need to see a doctor to have a safe abortion.
